args: Meee-yow! Tuna! Humongous fatty strips\nof tasty, tasty tuna!
I never thought I'd be able to come by\nsushi in this world, much less this\nsashimi-grade, A-plus, top-tier sushi!
I'm pleased you're happy with it; I learned\nfrom a true Hinomotoan chef, so it's good\nto know all that effort was worth it.
Now please, eat your fill. Call it my way\nof thanking you for catching that thief.
Ooooh, is this mackerel?! Sardines?!\nIt's an ocean of delicious fish\neverywhere I look!
You sure seem thrilled. You're like a totally\ndifferent person. Or cat, I guess.
Not a cat! But yes, I'm currently floating\non cloud nine. Heck, it's not every day I\ncan eat my dinner in the open!
Hey, that's right. Back in your world,\nyou had to pretend to be a normal cat\nthat didn't talk and all that, yeah?
Yep! That's why I always had to hide in\nJoker's bag and chow down in secret\nwhenever we went out to eat.
Um...we want you to teach us.
PLEASE TEACH US HOW TO BE\nPHANTOM THIEEEEEVES!
You kids wanna learn to be thieves?
Do you even know what\nphantom thieves are?
Yeah! They're people who're strong and\nSUPER cool!
Uh... I mean, you're not technically\nwrong about that, but...
You caught that one thief and it was RAD!
We wanna be cool like that!
Ha ha ha! Looks like you got\nyourself a nice little fan club!
Well, the fact they appreciate how cool\nI am makes me think they've got at least\na LITTLE promise...
Yeah, kids look up to their heroes—\nand to them, you're a TOTAL hero!
I, Mona, ace of the Phantom Thieves of\nHearts, shall become your coach\nand mentor!
Hey, Mona? Are you serious about this\nwhole ＂teaching little kids how to be\nphantom thieves＂ thing?
Don't worry, I won't teach them to steal.
To them, a phantom thief is a strong,\ncool hero, right?
Yeah, no. I was talking more about\nthe fact we have a mission to—
Now that it's decided, we must act!\nFollow me, my little thieflings!
Okay, did he forget the entire reason we\ncame to this town in the first place?
Right then! Lesson number one:\nA phantom thief must ALWAYS be cool.

I like that enthusiasm! Now, when it
comes to showing off coolness, the first
impression is critical—so let's
talk about your entry poses!
The Phantom Thieves of Hearts\nare on the scene!
Mewheheh! Cool, right?\nNow you guys try it.
No, no, no! You need to give it panache!\nPuff those chests out! Hold your head high!\nOh, but make sure it looks effortless.
Huh? We got it wrong again?\nGeez, this is kinda hard...
The way of the phantom thief is harsh\nand unyielding! You all must practice\nday and night without pause.
All right, you're really getting somewhere\nnow. Just make sure to stick your tails up!
Then how the heck are you going to\ntransform into a car?!
I can hardly recognize you anymore.\nYou're all phantom thieves for sure!
So we got super strong, too?
Aw, it was nothing. Any first-rate\nphantom thief knows that it's up to them\nto guide future generations! Nya ha ha!
That said, we had a long day of training.\nWe better get you home before your\nparents start to worry.
Coach, huh? Heh, kinda reminds me of\nback when I was teaching the rest of them\nthe basics of phantom thievery.
Hey, if you're done with all this coaching,\nwe need to be gettin' back.
Man, I love this town! The food's great,\nthe kids are nice, and it'll make a great\nstaging ground on the way to the capital!
While you were with the kids, I went\naround town gathering info. Apparently\nthe local lord is a real piece of work.
It means he's wringin' the poor folks here\ndry with unfair taxes and harsh laws.
I thought something was weird about\nhow slowly the townspeople reacted when\nthat thief showed up in broad daylight.
Okay, so what do we do? I mean,\nwe can't just ignore the situation.
Nope—but that doesn't mean there's\nan easy solution waiting for us.

This is Empire territory, so if we ain't
careful in how we get involved, we're
gonna be overrun with enemies before
we can say boo.
And no matter how bad this lord guy is,\nit'll still be a problem for the town if he's\nsuddenly gone.
Yeah, if I thought a good thrashing would\nfix things, I would've done it already.
Plus, our goal is to do recon here and help\nplan our Jail heist, which means we need\nto stay on the down-low.
I guess no matter what world you're in,\nthere's always some horrible adult\nruining it for people.
